questionsAndAnswers.question: What do I need to start my website?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: To get started, you'll need to provide a clear idea of your website’s purpose, content (text, images, videos), and any specific design preferences. If you have branding materials like a logo or color scheme, that will also be helpful.

questionsAndAnswers.question: Will the website be responsive across all devices?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Yes, I ensure that every website I design is fully responsive, meaning it will look and function perfectly on desktops, tablets, and smartphones.

questionsAndAnswers.question: Where will you build the website?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: I build websites using Webflow, WordPress, or GoDaddy platforms, depending on your needs and preferences. I will choose the best platform to match your requirements and goals.

questionsAndAnswers.question: How long will it take to complete my website?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: The timeline depends on the complexity of the project. Generally, a standard website can be completed within 2 to 4 weeks. For more complex sites, the timeline will be adjusted accordingly.

questionsAndAnswers.question: Can I make changes to the website after it’s built?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Absolutely! I provide training and support to help you make changes and updates to your website. Additionally, I offer ongoing maintenance services if needed.
